<br>
What im wondering is how much worse is the lag there?  In EQ, with my 433 MH prossor and 96 mb of ram, i got quite a bit of lag in most areas so im kinda reluctant to get AO cus it sounds like even more lag than EQ.<br>
<br>
Well anyway,  any thoughts to this problem?  Much appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustrizz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Strizz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/13/01 9:11:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.fortunecity.com/bennyhills/pun/190/jetsonelroyjetson4.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> you won't like to hear this, but regardless of what Funcom may say, you absolutely MUST have 512 MB of RAM to enjoy the game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uronaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ronaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/01 12:26:42 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> I started AO about 1 week ago with a 433 celeron, 256 megs, ATI radeon 64 meg.<br>
<br>
Huge problems with graphical lag and general lag in cities / crowded areas.<br>
Yesterday, I upgraded to an Athlon 1GHz, and have noticed a HUGE increase in performance.<br>
<br>
I recommend:<br>
<br>
- more RAM (256 cost about 20$ over here in germany right now, no big thing)<br>
- faster CPU (my athlon cost ~100$, plus a new mainboard which cost another 90$ or so, plus a new cooler/fan for ~25$) <br>
<br>
You wouldn't enjoy the game much without serious upgrades. If you can afford it, do it. Hardware is dirt cheap at the moment. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.jsp?num=964>Ronaan<a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujerehko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerehko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/01 1:59:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> Well, 512 is quite an overstatement...but...384 will do you just fine.<br>
<br>
I'm running a 1gHz Intel platform, GeForce 2 32mb, 7200rpm drive. Up until two weeks ago, I had 128 megs of ram, in that state on this machine the game was crippling. I added the additional 256 and wham, no more hangs, lockups...etc.<br>
<br>
The game is quite playable now, but I'll warn you...the weight of Funcom's &quot;Nerf-StickTM&quot; is quite a bit heavier than Verent's and they just may ruin the game if their next patch goes live from test. <p>Dominick 'Jerehko' Arnall<br><b>Omni-Tek Surgical Eliminations Specialist</b><br><i>
"Making clanners send me incoherent tells since 29,473!"</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarmeister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarmeister</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/01 1:53:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> Wow thanks for the nice responses!<br>
<br>
I had no idea computers were getting so cheap.  I bought mine 2 years ago for 600 with 400 rebate (woohoo!) and my dad just bought a nice 600 mh one for $600 a few months ago so i figured i was still gonna be spending some money to upgrade.<br>
<br>
So you say its cheaper just to buy individual systems?  I know the basics about computer hardware (at least i think...) but what you said didnt make 100% sense.  <br>
<br>
Also, you dont buy from regular store do you?  Any thought to what type of store to look in or order from?  Though they might be different in germany.<br>
<br>
Anyway,  hope im not too much of a bother and thanks for the help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukoru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Koru</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/01 2:05:47 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> Well, the current RAM is gonna hurt you pretty bad. I'm on a 500MHz P3 with 256 MB RAM and I get what I call the PowerPoint Slides Show when I enter populated areas of the city, I'm literally hearing my machine try to cope. Missions I get some lag in, mostly in entering some rooms. It runs ok though on minimum settings, but playing on minimum settings isn't much fun in a game as pretty as this. Without the RAM I dread to think how the game would work. I know I'm definately upgrading my CPU as well, as I gather that makes the big difference if your RAM is 256 MB or higher. Heck, one of the big computer stores here has 256 RAM for sale for $40, so I'll upgrade that too since it's fairly cheap - about the price of one game - yet makes so much difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uronaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ronaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/01 2:49:12 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> Ya, well,<br>
<br>
RAM as it is, is fairly cheap at the moment.<br>
Everything else is pretty cheap as well, if you don't head for the top-of-the-line gear.<br>
<br>
As I said, 256 mb ram ~20$ US<br>
1GHz AMD Athlon ~100$ US<br>
motherboard ~90$ US<br>
Cooler/fan combo ~20$ US<br>
<br>
I noticed a HUGE and I mean <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> HUGE</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> increase in performace going from 433 celeron to 1ghz athlon.<br>
<br>
Your video card is a crucial point as well.<br>
Try to have a good 32mb card. 64 will be better.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
As to where I buy, there is one store near the place I live that sells single components. Find one of those near your place...<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.jsp?num=964>Ronaan<a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarmeister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarmeister</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/01 1:18:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> I still cant believe how in the dark i was about all this.  I didnt even think RAM did much unless you had an overloaded computer.  I definitely know what im buying as soon as i find a place that sells it.<br>
<br>
Thanks very much for all your help from all of you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujerehko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerehko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/01 5:53:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> Hehe, you did have an overloaded computer...you were running AO right? lol<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
 <p>Dominick 'Jerehko' Arnall<br><b>Omni-Tek Surgical Eliminations Specialist</b><br><i>
"Making clanners send me incoherent tells since 29,473!"</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslymmpikkins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slymm Pikkins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/01 4:55:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> RAM is like money; you can never have enough.<br>
<br>
I have an athlon 700, with 384MB and a 32MB matrox g400. It's definitely playable, gets choppy running around in Tir sometimes, but its not horrible.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sounder<br>
Fixer<br>
RK1 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukelliv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelliv</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/01 7:56:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AO system requirment</span><hr size=1> OK is the game still jerky in cities? I have an Athlon T-Bird with 512MB and at times (month ago) it would choke MY system. Oh I have a Geo2 as well...12.40 drivers (the 12.90drives HOSED my system).<br>
